S14: INT. HOSPITAL WAITING ROOM - NIGHT

elements.text: MADISON walks up to her door, arms full of paint supplies and groceries. There's an eviction notice from the City Marshall and a chain and lock on the door.

lines.text: Shit! I thought I had two more days. Damn it!

elements.text: Madison drops the supplies on the floor and takes out here cell phone. She makes a call
SOUND EFFECT: RINGING
The answering machine picks up.

lines.text: Jason pick up it's me. Jason come on I need you. I know you're there.

elements.text: Madison puts away the phone and picks up her supplies.
CUT TO
Madison struggles to retrieve the keys to Jason's apartment out of her pocket while juggling her supplies. She gets the door open.
As soon as she enters the apartment she hears the unmistakable moans and groans of wild sex coming from the bedroom.

Madison heads back for the door but hesitates. She puts her supplies down quietly and then opens a large can of paint. She walks to the bedroom, flings the door open and throws the paint all over Jason and his lover.

lines.text: What the fuck!

elements.text: Jason wipes globs of paint from his face.

lines.text: Madison! Is that you honey, wait I can explain.

elements.text: Madison beams the empty paint can directly at Jason's head. It hits the mark and knocks Jason out. Madison storms out of the apartment.
CUT TO
A small low lite funeral home is filled with Black mourners. There's crying and carrying on. DESMOND is draped over a coffin in the front on the home.

He is holding the hand of the deceased, his baby brother. Desmond is crying and mumbling incoherently. Suddenly his cell phone rings. Everyone looks shocked. Desmond lets the phone ring a few times, then composes himself and answers it.

lines.text: Hello. Hey Madison how are you. Oh no what's wrong. That bastard. Listen baby it's really not a good time. You need how much. Alright I got you. Pick you up? When? Alright I'll be there. Alright baby, have a good flight.

elements.text: Desmond hangs up the phone. Everyone is starring in absolute disbelief. Desmond looks at them, then turns back to his brother and starts crying loudly like before.
Everyone goes back to crying and carrying on then Desmond's cell phone rings again.
CUT TO
Jetta is a beautiful black women sporting a tank top and plenty of tattoos. She is escorted back to her cell by a correction officer.

lines.text: Pack up your shit Jetta. I'll be back for you in a couple of hours after the paper work clears.
I'll be here.

elements.text: The C.O. walks away and before the door to the cell closes two female inmates slip into Jetta's cell. The door slams close.

lines.text: Heard they letting you out bitch. I got a going away gift for your ass.

elements.text: The two inmates pull out home-made shanks.
CUT TO
Moments later the C.O. returns and opens the cell door.
The two inmates that snuck in are laying on the floor unconscious. Jetta's stuff is packed up and she approaches the door.

lines.text: I'm finished here

elements.text: CUT TO
FIFTH is speeding down New York city streets. He is being chased by Private Investigators, a fire truck and the Police. Fifth has a huge smile on his face.
He turns on the music and appears to have heavy bandages on both wrist. As Fifth speeds around a corner a cute girl catches his attention and he takes his eyes off the road.

When Fifth looks forward he sees a kid running across the street. Fifth swerves to avoid the kid and collides into a double parked car. Fifth is shaken up but composes himself and jumps out of the car.
Fifth hears the approaching sirens and looks around for a building to run into. He spots one and sprints into it. The police and fire engine speed up to the scene of the collision.
Fifth sprints up the stairs to the roof. The Investigators give chase but can't keep up with him. Once on the roof Fifth throws off his suit jacket revealing a “LIFE IS BEAUTIFUL” T-shirt.
The investigators reach the roof.

lines.text: Mr. Mann please don't do it

elements.text: Fifth sees them and sprints to the edge of the roof and leaps off.
CUT TO
Desmond is still in his black suit from the funeral. He's speeding on the highway headed upstate. He's jamming to some music when the phone rings.
Des looks at the phone with discuss and let's it ring a few times before he answer's it.

lines.text: Hello. How are you Dr. Mitchell. What happened now. Ah huh. Ah huh. (Laughing) He did what. Are you shitting me? Ah huh. He's alive? Well listen Dr. Mitchell his sister is flying in tonight and I know she'll want to see him. I see. Is there any chance he can be released to her. With medication. I see. Alright then Dr. Mitchell thank you.

elements.text: Desmond puts down the cell phone and keeps driving.
Moments later Desmond pulls up to the release gate of the women's penitentiary that Jetta served time at. Jetta comes out.
Desmond gets out of the car and approaches Jetta. They give each other a short kiss on the lips and hug.

lines.text: Jetta it's good to see you.
You too Des. Thanks for picking me up.
Don't mention it. Let's get the hell out of here. I hate prisons.
Yeah. Me too.

elements.text: Jetta and Des get in the car and drive off. Jetta has a manila envelope with some small possessions in it. She reaches into the envelope and pulls out a marriage band. Jetta is starring at the band. Des looks over at her. Jetta calmly rolls down her window and throws the band out of it.

lines.text: Your a free woman Jetta

I may be out of prison but I'm not free. A free person can do whatever they want to. I want to hold my son and I can't. I want to go home and be held by my husband and I can't. I don't even have a home to go home to.

elements.text: Desmond tries to reassure Jetta with his eyes. Jetta cracks a small smile.

lines.text: We're not to far away. I can always take you back.
(Smiling) fuck you Des. What's with the suit?
Oh I was at a funeral earlier.
Earlier when?
Around the time you called
Oh my God Des I'm so sorry. Why did you answer the phone.
The caller I.D. said unavailable and I thought it was a call I was expecting. I had to take it.
Who died.
Not died. Killed. My baby brother.
Pop! Oh no. What happened Des
Pop was involved with some crazy shit. Damn cops don't know the whole story. I got an investigator looking into it for me. When I find out who killed my brother I'm going to kill the muthafucka.

elements.text: Jetta looks at Des with concern.

lines.text: Stop playing Des. I don't want to have to visit you in jail.
I'm serious. The mutha fucka is dead. You won't be visiting me in jail because I don't plan on getting caught.
I'll help you

elements.text: Des looks at Jetta like she is crazy.

lines.text: What the fuck are they smoking in prison these days. You must be kidding. You just got out
I thought you didn't plan on getting caught?
Don't be a wise ass.

I'm not. I'm serious. Besides I'm not talking about helping you kill him. I'm talking about helping you. Get control over yourself Des. You see where revenge got me. Five years. Even if you don't get caught that kind of shit catches up to you.
Don't give me that shit Jetta. Put that energy into finding your son.
Please don't bring that up Des. I can't deal with that.
I'm sorry. I didn't mean it that way. All I'm saying is no matter where he's at your still his mother.
I said I don't want to talk about Marlon god damn it Des. It's over! He's gone. I made my choice.

elements.text: Jetta sits back in her seat and turns her head to look out the window.
CUT TO
FLASHBACK SEQUENCE - Jetta catches Mr. Gathers
Mr. Gathers the third grade teacher is huddled in the corner of his classroom. Jetta has a large hand gun aimed at him.

lines.text: I didn't touch him. I swear it. I didn't touch him. He's confused.
Now you know fear. You're an animal! You'll never put your hands on another innocent child.
I'm not lying. Just put the gun down
Shut the fuck up. I don't want to hear your lies.

elements.text: Mr. Gathers tries to rush Jetta. She fires off shots and hits him in the head. Brain matter and blood splatter on the window of his classroom door. Students standing outside, staring through the glass start running and screaming.
CUT TO
Jetta is clinching onto her son as the police pulled him away from her and handcuff her. She is screaming and crying and trying to get back to her son.
FADE OUT
Des pulls into a parking space and turns the car off. Jetta wakes from her sleep.

lines.text: We're are we?
We're at the airport. We're picking up Madison.
Des I'm sorry I yelled at you.
Don't sweat it baby. Do me a favor
What is it.
Shut up and listen for one minute.

elements.text: Jetta looks at Des with surprise.

lines.text: You're being a selfish bitch. A boy needs his mother. I won't let you sit here and give up on being a part of his life. You're out of prison now. You should have left that woe is me bullshit there. You ain't the first mother to serve time and you damn sure won't be the last. You said you want to help me. Help me by finding that boy and letting him know that you're there for him.
You're right Des I am being selfish.

elements.text: They arrive at the airport. Des parks near the terminal and gets out. Jetta follows. She walks over to Des and gives him a hug. She then backs up and sucker punches him square in the stomach.

lines.text: That's for calling me a bitch.

elements.text: Des bends over from the blow. Then he laughs out loud. The two walk into the terminal. Moments later they walk out with Madison. Madison is running her mouth and Des appears very annoyed.

lines.text: You're still driving that old Cadillac Des. It's the Twenty first century. Why don't you get a new car.
Why don't you stop borrowing money from me so I can actually afford a new car Madi. Damn. I forgot how fuckin annoying you are. I still love you. You just annoy the hell out of me.

elements.text: Madison looks shocked. Jetta is laughing

lines.text: I can't believe how muscular you've gotten Jetta. How did you do that. Yoga?
Prison.

elements.text: Madison is taken back

lines.text: Oh. I hope it was someone I hate?

elements.text: Des puts the luggage in the trunk. Madison jumps into the front seat. Des comes around to his door and sees Madison in the front seat.

lines.text: Oh hell no. You're not sitting in the front with me.
Oh Des stop playing
I'm not playing. Scoot your ass to the back.

elements.text: Madison gets out and gets in the back. Jetta gets in the front. They drive off.

lines.text: So then I hit him with the paint can and knocked his sorry ass out. That little hussy of his just sat there.
So I take it the engagement is off.
That's not funny Desmond. I really loved him.
I'm sorry Madi. How's the painting going.
That's what brings me here.. I was working on my best piece yet when I got evicted from my studio
You got evicted, what happened?
What happened is Madi doesn't believe in paying her own bills. When are you going to get a real job
Stop it Des. She's a starving artist
Artist maybe, starving definitely not. You could stand to lose a few pounds Madi.
Go to hell Des. Now I know why I left New York.
Because of me?
You and that crazy ass brother of mine. Speaking of Fifth where is he.
What do mean where is he? You know damn well he's in the hospital. When's the last time you called the hospital Madi?
That's what he has you for Des. I'm not going to raise my blood pressure over Fifth anymore. If he wants to kill himself he's not going to take me with him.
Don't tell me Fifth's still suicidal.
He's just a little confused. I'm talking some since into him.
Four Ph.D. psychologists can't talk since to him but you can Des.
Damn right.
Well you deserve each other. I told you before and I'll tell you again, it doesn't take ten years to commit suicide. My brother just wants attention.
As usual Madi you don't know what the hell your talking about. I came this close to losing my best friend today.

elements.text: CUT TO
FLASHBACK SEQUENCE - Fifth takes flight
BLAINE WELLWORTH is the cofounder and current President of an investment firm that he started with Fifth. Blaine is at the hospital today to visit Fifth
He is walking down the hallway to Fifth's room with Dr. Mitchell a long legged gorgeous psychiatrist.

lines.text: How is he doctor?
He's suicidal. Last week we let him in the garden to get some fresh air.

The orderly turned his back for a second and Mr. Mann tried to hang himself from a tree with his pants. One minute longer and he would have affixciated We have him under twenty four hour surveillance in a soft room now.
Can I go in the room? I need to speak to him about matters of a very confidential nature.
Sure but he will have to remain restrained. Do you have any foreign objects on you.
Well I have this heirloom pen, and my eye glasses . That's it.

elements.text: Dr. Mitchell snatches the glasses from Blaine's face. She holds out her hand for the pen and Blaine gives it to her.

lines.text: Is that it.
Yes I believe so.

elements.text: They arrive at the room. An orderly meets them at the door. Blaine peeks in through the glass and sees Fifth, restrained by a straight jacket dancing around in the room.

lines.text: Why's he dancing like that?
Because he's crazy.

elements.text: The orderly opens the door and Blaine walks in. The door closes behind him. Dr. Mitchell walks off

lines.text: Hey Blaine. How's it hanging?
It's hanging well, thank you very much.
What brings you here today Blaine. Hey nice suit.

Thank you. I'm here to talk business Fifth. I really think you should reconsider my offer. Dr. Mitchell told me about the incident in the garden. Really Fifth if you insist on killing yourself at least think about the hundreds of hard working people the firm employs.
You mean like you Blaine. What's wrong Blaine six cars and the mansion in Bronxville not enough for you.

It's not about me Fifth. You know that. These are tough times. The firm can't afford to pay out twenty million dollars on an insurance premium if you die. Please reconsider our settlement offer to breach the contract.

You're right Blaine. What was I thinking. I owe it to the employees. I don't want to see them out of work. It's the med's Blaine. They just keep drugging me up. It's got my head all smoky. I can't think straight half of the time.
Maybe I can talk to Dr. Mitchell.
No! She's the leader. She's had it in for me since day one. I turned down her advances and before I knew it she had me more doped up than Robert Downey. Fuck!

elements.text: Fifth starts dancing around again

lines.text: What is it.
My balls itch. Hey Blaine I don't suppose I could impose on you.
Certainly not.

elements.text: Fifth continues to dance around

lines.text: Fifth about the insurance.
Can't think about that right now Blaine. You ever have itchy balls and couldn't scratch them. Shit! Drives me crazy.
Perhaps I could free one hand. Then it's back to business.
Of course.

elements.text: Blaine unfastens a strap. Fifth turns away to scratch his balls. He starts moving around sporadically

lines.text: Ooohh! That's it. Ooohh that's good.

elements.text: Blaine approaches Fifth. Fifth looks out the corner of his eye and sees Blaine approaching. He turns and strikes Blaine square in the chin. Blaine is knocked out.
Fifth unfastens the other arm and removes the straight jacket. He undresses Blaine and puts him the straight jacket.
Fifth arranges Blaine in the corner so his face is hidden. He bangs on the door to alert the orderly

lines.text: Orderly come quick.

elements.text: The Orderly opens the door and rushes in. He spots Blaine in the corner and doesn't think to look up at Fifth.

lines.text: I think he swallowed his tongue or something.

elements.text: Fifth sneaks out the door and down the hallway. As he runs out of the facility the alarms go off. Fifth digs around in the jacket pocket and retrieves some cars keys. He looks around in the lot and spots the shiny convertible Mustang. He jumps in and takes off.
Two investigators are sitting in a parked car in the hospital's parking lot. They see Fifth jump in the Mustang and they take off after him.
CUT TO
Fifth is starring at the ledge. On his T-shirt reads "LIFE IS BEAUTIFUL" in bold letters. Behind him are the two investigators hired by his firm to prevent him from committing suicide.
Fifth ignores their pleas and runs to the ledge and leaps. The investigators don't react. From the ground looking up Fifth comes careening to the street.
The Firefighters have brought out a large net. They catch Fifth in it. The police grab Fifth and handcuff him. The two investigators come rushing up and watch as Fifth is taken away.
FADE TO

lines.text: Holy shit!
Those investigators have stopped Fifth at least a dozen times. They're the best.
But Des honey. What makes you think that you can talk Fifth out of killing himself.
I can't. If I can help keep him alive until he wakes the fuck up then he'll cut the crazy shit out. At least I hope so

elements.text: Des looks at Jetta through the rear view mirror. She makes eye contact back at him.

lines.text: I know you don't want to see your friend die Des but

But what Madi. And he's not just my friend. He's your fucking brother. Hell I remember you being a lot more concerned before he gave away all his money. It seems like you always find yourself back here when dead fucking broke.

Fuck you Des. That's not fair. You know I love my brother. You think I want to see him dead. I've going through this shit for years. Since he first tried at fifteen. I was there. You weren't. It's like a sick movie that just keeps dragging on. I'm tired Des. That doesn't mean I don't love my brother.
Good. You're get a chance to prove it.
Prove it how.
Only you can sign him out. I spoke to Dr. Mitchell earlier and she and I agree that seeing you might help him.
What do you mean sign him out.
She'll sign him over to your care. You'll be responsible. Don't worry. The investigators will be on him like white on rice. It'll be fine

elements.text: Desmond pulls into the parking lot of the Mental hospital where Fifth is being treated. Everybody exits the car and enter the hospital.
The Night watchmen is a young guy with heads phones on sitting behind a desk with video monitors. He's so into the music he doesn't see the group enter.
Des pulls out a stick of gum and balls up the wrapper. He throws it at the guard who is startled.

lines.text: I'm sorry visiting hours are over.
Listen eagle eye we're hear to pick up a discharged patient. Fifth Mann
Fifth Mann? I need the entire name The guard picks up a list and looks at it.

Fuck me! That is the real name. And I thought Black people had some crazy names. It says here that he can only be released into the custody of Madison Mann. Oh I get it. Fifth and Madison, that's cute.

elements.text: Everyone flashes the guard a dirty, disgusted look.

lines.text: That's me. I'm Madison Mann
I'll need to see some ID.

elements.text: CUT TO

Everyone is seated waiting for Fifth to be brought out. The Guard goes back to bobbing and bouncing to his music. Moments later Fifth is brought out by a large Orderly and a very sleepy looking doctor. The doctor hands Madison a form to sign.

lines.text: Oh shit the gang's all here. It's the reunion of the broken hearts club.

elements.text: The orderly removes the restraints from Fifth and he immediately gives his sister a huge hug.

lines.text: This is a surprise Madi. You came to New York to see me.

elements.text: Des looks at Madi as if daring her to lie.

lines.text: That and other things Fifth. I'm telling you right now you're not going to try no crazy shit with me.
I got it Madi. Nothing crazy.

elements.text: Fifth has a mischievous look on his face.

lines.text: It's good to see you.

elements.text: Fifth releases Madison and embraces Des.

lines.text: Hey Superman.
Des the mon'. What it is Bro. I'm sorry about Pop. Dr. Mitchell told me. How you doing?
I been better.
What happened to Pop?
Pop was shot and killed last week Madi. His funeral was this morning.
Desmond why didn't you say something. Please don't tell me I called you at the funeral.
I didn't say anything because you didn't ask. Forget about it

elements.text: Madison goes over to give Des a hug. At first he looks annoyed and doesn't hug her back. Then he smiles and hugs her back.

lines.text: Jetta look at you. Been working out huh.
A little something.

elements.text: Jetta and Fifth posture and square up like they're about to box each other. Jetta hits Fifth in the arm and he pretends it's broke.

lines.text: Hey they'll be none of that in here. This is a hospital.
You're not the boss of me. Come on club. Let's get the hell out of here. This place is for crazy people.

elements.text: The club file out of the hospital one by one.

lines.text: Hey can I drive?

elements.text: Des mushes Fifth in the head

lines.text: There's your answer

elements.text: Everyone jumps in the Cadi with Des in the driver seat.

lines.text: I don't know about the rest of you but I could kill for a cheese burger.

elements.text: Everybody looks back at Jetta.

lines.text: I mean I could really go for a good cheese burger. I haven't had a decent meal in five years.
Really where you been Jet?
I was in jail Fifth.
Get the fuck out! You didn't tell me Des.
Yes I did mutha fucka. Those meds' are scrambling your brain. Where do you live?
Wait a minute. I know where I live. Oh shit I can't remember.
I'm going to have a talk with that doctor of yours tomorrow.
So if you were in jail then where is Marlon?

elements.text: Jetta looks down. Her whole mood changes. She begins to look out the window and wipes away a tear

lines.text: Do me a favor Fifth.
Shut up?
You're a mind reader.

elements.text: The mood in the car is somber. No one says a word. Fifth clears his throat and Des flashes him a look.
CUT TO
The club sit at a booth. The mood is still somber and no one has anything to say. Jetta is playing with her straw in her drink waiting for the food to come.

lines.text: It feels funny to be on the outside. Five fucking years is a along time. Fuck it. It was worth it to have one less monster in the world. I'd do it again if I had to. My only regret is I lost my family. I miss my baby. Five years with seeing your child is torture. I'm sorry guys

elements.text: Jetta looks out the window and wipes away some tears. The waitress serves Jetta's food and she begins to eat.

lines.text: That looks good. I should have ordered that. I'm starving. Where the hell is my food. I haven't eaten in two days. I never wanted to do the starving artist literally. You're right Des. I'm broke, I'm homeless. My work sucks, my fucking life stinks.

elements.text: Madi looks totally dejected. The waitress brings Madison's food. Her face lights up

lines.text: Finally

elements.text: Madison pigs out.
Everyone is quiet again. Fifth looks like he is about to start his confessional but just as he opens his mouth the waitress returns with his food. He starts to eat.

lines.text: So I guess we're all crashing at your place tonight Des.
Over my dead body Madi. I've got the keys to Fifth's loft in my pocket. You and superman are going home. Jetta your welcome to crash with me if you want.

elements.text: The waitress brings the check. Desmond looks around the table for contributions.

lines.text: Don't look at me.
I had to borrow plane-fare.

elements.text: Des looks at Fifth.

lines.text: What I didn't give away you took. I'm running on empty.
Just like old times. A bunch of broke muthafuckas.

elements.text: Desmond pulls a few bills out of his pocket and drops them on the table.
CUT TO
Fifth and Madison stumble out of the car and walk into the lobby of the building.

lines.text: Good night guys. Thank you Des. I'll call you tomorrow.

elements.text: Des speeds off. Minutes later he pulls up to his brownstone. He looks around for a parking space but can't find one.

lines.text: I'm to tired for this shit

elements.text: Desmond double parks and turns the car off.

lines.text: This isn't a spot. What are you doing
I've been driving all fucking day. I'm tired as fuck. I'll move it in the morning.

elements.text: Des and Jetta get out of the car. As they approach the stairs to the Brownstone they see three figures waiting for them.

lines.text: Bubble? Bubble what the hell are you doing on my stoop at two in the morning.
I'm waiting for you son.
Listen I'm too tired for this bullshit. Get your fake thug ass off my stoop. And take those hip hop pirates with you.
We got business to discuss. You know how we do. Pop had an outstanding debt and as his nearest to kin you gotta cover.
I just buried my brother today and you come around here showing your nuts.
Business is business.

elements.text: Des steps forward aggressively. Bubbles pulls back his jacket revealing a handgun.

lines.text: Oh! It's like that?
It's like that

elements.text: Bubble pulls the gun out and points it at Jetta.

lines.text: Five G's Des. Bizness' is Bizness'
You think I got that kinda cash laying around.
For your homegirls' sake I hope you do. I won't kill you cause I want my doe. You want her to live you better go in there and come back out with five grand.
I see where you coming from. Alright I'll be right back.

elements.text: Des walks enters the brownstone. Jetta waits outside.

lines.text: Don't worry shorty.

elements.text: Jetta smirks.
CUT TO
Des walks into his apartment. He turns the lights on in his kitchen. He reaches behind his back and pulls out a .45 Caliber handgun. He places it on the kitchen counter.
Then he pulls open a drawer full off tools and grabs a roofing ax.

He walks back down the long hallway to the door. Minutes later Desmond and Jetta come through the door. Des throws down the roofing ax on the table. It's stained with blood. Jetta goes into the living room.
Des walks into the kitchen and grabs a couple of glasses and a bottle of Jack Daniels. He walks into the living room.
Jetta looks exhausted and has blood on her shirt. Des pours some whisky into both cups and hands one to Jetta.
He gulps down what's in his cup then grabs the bottle and gulps that down too.

lines.text: Thanks
Don't mention it. What was that all about.
Some kid Pop scrambled with. Stupid young muthafucka. This new millennium hip hop shit has these punks thinking they like it raw.
How about some hard core

elements.text: They both laugh

lines.text: I don't know about you but I'm through. I'm about to pass out. I gotta get some sleep.
I wanted to talk to you.
We can talk in the morning. You can have the bed tonight. After that it's the couch.
I think I'm going to take a bath before I get in bed.
Knock yourself out

elements.text: Desmond stumbles to the linen closet and grabs a blanket.
Jetta walks slowly into the bathroom to take a bath.
FADE OUT
INT/EXT. FIFTH'S LOFT - DAY
Fifth is on the roof of his building starring at the sunrise. He's dangerously close to the edge but seems un-phased by this. A huge smile lights up his face.
Fifth moves away from the ledge and exits the roof. Back inside his apartment he walks to the fridge and grabs a carton of orange juice. He heads toward the bathroom.

Madison is nestled comfortably on the sofa surrounded by pillows. She is woken by the crashing sound of running water. Fifth is drawing water for a bath. Madison drags herself into the bathroom. Fifth is lounging in the bathtub. Madison pulls her panties down and plops on the toilet. Her pee is quite loud.

lines.text: Morning brother dear.
Morning sis. How did you sleep.
I slept great. There's something about New York nights that make me sleep like a baby. How did you sleep.
I didn't. I sat up on the roof and waited for the sun
That's beautiful. Stay off the roof!

elements.text: Madison notices the heavy bandages on both of Fifth's wrists. She frowns

lines.text: Fifth. What's this?
I know, I know. I'm sorry Madi I know you don't want to see me hurt.
That's not even it Fifth. How can you hurt yourself like that. What goes through your mind when your slicing your arteries open.
The ends justify the means. I know I don't belong here so I do what I need to do to end it.
But you're still here.
I know. Crazy isn't it. I've been close a couple of times.
Shut up. I don't want to hear it. What would mom say Fifth. If she were still alive you would have killed her by now.
Madi you can't live life for someone else. When I was fifteen I made the decision to end it all. You and Mom interfered and I've been trying ever since. Life simply holds no meaning to me Madi
I don't understand. You're young, women fall all over themselves for you, you were filthy rich and your my brother. You have it all.
That's it all to you Madison. If that's it all then why don't you want that.
Because that's not what I want.

So what makes you think that it's what I want. I made all that money for Mom. I wanted her to have her dream and to live the life she always envied. She had her penthouse, she had her private showings at Tiffany's. None of that shit means anything to me.
What's so bad about your life
I'm just not feeling it.
That's stupid
That's your opinion Madison. I've never criticized the way you live. The jerks you chose to throw your heart at.
There's a difference. I'm not trying to kill myself.
A minor difference.

elements.text: Madison gets up and flushes the toilet.

lines.text: Here we go
What.
There's a leak under the tub. Every time you flush the toilet or let water out of the tub it leaks downstairs.
Why don't you get it fixed
I've been meaning to but my hands were tied.

elements.text: Sure enough loud banging can be heard on the floor. The women is yelling

lines.text: (Filtered from downstairs) You asshole.Why don't you get that pipe fixed. You're fucking up my prints.
(Yelling) blow it out your ear. You old hag.
Is she an old hag?
Hell if I know. I've never met her.
What do you mean you've never met her. How long has she been living here.
She moved in around the same time as me. I'm not exactly the socializing type Madi. I spend most of my time in a padded room. Besides, she sounds like a hag.
You need to go talk to her

lines.text: Des get the phone. Des

lines.text: All the other kids in the neighborhood went to Sunday school. Mom took me and Madi to Bergdorff, then Saks and we finished off at Bloomy's. To her that was spiritual.

I would have been more worried for you than mom. She was really a little touched.

elements.text: Sidney laughs

lines.text: It's strange.

I hope she was. Everything I had I owed to her. She never wanted for anything. But I know none of that made her happy.
I could see you as the good son

I lost the will.

Anything
How did you know I was lying.
(smiling) Your body language, your voice, but mostly your eyes.
So you can tell when people are lying to you.
Not people. Just you
If I wasn't in love with you I'd be a little freaked out.

lines.text: Hey pull up over here I need to grab something real quick.
Let me find a spot and I'll come with you

lines.text: Oh my stars. I don't believe it. Come here, come here. Give me a kiss

lines.text: Noah come out here it's Fifth. Fifth is here

lines.text: You think she'll like it.
Do I think she'll like it? My boy. With that ring you could propose to a dozen women. All at once

elements.text: Mrs. Peacle pokes her husband

lines.text: No no. Put your money away
I can't accept a gift like this
My boy. I love you, but not that much. Your mother paid for it. It's yours.

lines.text: A tip. For the best jewelers in town.

elements.text: Fifth puts the ring back in it's velvet and gold box.

lines.text: Wait. What's her size? We need to fit it for her.

I just want to surprise her. After I ask her then we'll come back together. I hope she says yes.
Do you love her?
Oh yeah.

Two days.

elements.text: Mr and Mrs. Peacle make eye contact

lines.text: Let me give you your receipt.

Nothing. The store was closed
You lie!

Okay I'll go for it.

Yes

Uhhhhh! Yes

elements.text: Sidney is stunned. Her expression borders on fear but transforms to joy. It further transforms to absolute elation as Fifth presents her with the box. Sidney takes the box. lines.text: Yes!

lines.text: Yes Fifth Mann I would be honored to be your wife. I love you

lines.text: I know it probably doesn't fit but we can go back

elements.text: Fifth slides the ring on her left ring finger and the fit is perfect

lines.text: Perfect.
Where are we off too.
We have to celebrate.

Yeah. I can't wait to tell Madi and Des Sidney starts up the car and the speed off. She is distracted by the ring and repeatedly takes her eyes off the road to stare at it. Fifth is once again starring up at the clouds.

A sharp pain. I just got a really sharp pain in my chest Des is feeling his chest
I'll take of care this. You just go sit down.
Thank you.
